               </h4>
               <p>Indonesia’s manufacturing sector is expanding rapidly across automotive, chemicals, and consumer goods. We benchmark cost structures, production efficiency, and innovation adoption across industrial estates in Java, Sumatra, and Sulawesi.</p>
               <p>Our analysis compares Indonesia’s manufacturing performance against ASEAN peers such as Vietnam, Thailand, and Malaysia, helping organizations understand key advantages in labor availability, domestic market scale, and resource access. These insights enable manufacturers and policymakers to improve productivity and attract higher-value investments.</p>
